Making this interactive _should_ be pretty straightforward. In particular, redeemers can challenge clients with a per-token context, e.g.,

```
struct {
   opaque redeemer_nonce[32]; // 32 fresh random bytes
   uint64 timestamp;  // Seconds since UNIX epoch 
} TokenContext;
```

When generating a token request, clients can then form the message to be signed as: 

```
struct {
   opaque client_nonce[32]; // 32 fresh random bytes
   TokenContext context; // Copied from above
} TokenInput;

...

blinded_req, blind_inv = rsabssa_blind(ORIGIN_KEY, TokenInput)
```

`TokenContext` should be bound to the client session, e.g., discarded when the session goes away. @dvorak42, what do you think?

