The main point, from the issue, was not to prevent the client-origin communication from having an intermediary watching things, but to stop the intermediary from harvesting tokens that it could then use in _other_ connections/sessions/contexts as its own client.

If the origin can require that the challenge/nonce is specific to a given session, can't it prove that this wasn't a token harvested on behalf of an unrelated connection?

